==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*παιδίον / paidion / pahee-dee'-on

===Etymology===
*Neuter diminutive of [[παῖς]]; a child (of either sex), that is, (properly) an infant, or (by extension) a half grown boy or girl; figuratively an immature Christian:

===Noun===
'''παιδίον'''

# (little, young) [[child]], [[damsel]].

